SIMPLE: whir
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whir
<hw>Whir</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Whirred</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Whirring</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Perhaps of imitative origin;
cf. D. <ets>hvirre</ets> to whirl, and E. <ets>hurr</ets>,
<ets>hurry</ets>, <ets>whirl</ets>. <?/<?/<?/.]</ety> <def>To whirl
round, or revolve, with a whizzing noise; to fly or more quickly with a
buzzing or whizzing sound; to whiz.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The partridge bursts away on <qex>whirring</qex> wings.</q>
<rj><qau>Beattie.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whir</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Whir
<hw>Whir</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Whir</er> to whiz.]</ety>
<def>To hurry a long with a whizzing sound.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This world to me is like a lasting storm,⟦br⟧
<qex>Whirring</qex> me from my friends.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whir</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Whir
<hw>Whir</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A buzzing or whizzing sound produced
by rapid or whirling motion; <as>as, the <ex>whir</ex> of a partridge;
the <ex>whir</ex> of a spinning wheel.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whirl</ent>⟦br⟧
